Circa 2013 @jaronboyer @crowellzach and I wrote “Hell Of A Night”, that was later recorded by my buddy @dustinlynchmusic 
Zach and I happen to be out on the bus writing for DL’s next album, when in Syracuse, NY one night, I decided to play him the demo. At the time, it was on hold for another artist, but DL was bound and determined to record the song. Fast forward to it taking 56 weeks, it became my second #1 single as a songwriter. #HellOfANight

🥃 YOU NEVER FORGET YOUR FIRST 🥃 The day I met @coleswindell I knew our friendship would be something special. Together we wrote ‘Aint Worth The Whiskey’ with our buddy @joshmartincountry and it later because my first #1 song as a songwriter. Who would’ve thought that 3 guys, that were green as they could be, but had an absolute love for country music, would write a song from the heart about a bad breakup, that would later take 4 years before it ever saw the light of day. #AintWorthTheWhiskey
Gonna put a little out there in the high beams, and just let ‘er eat… 🛻💨 #RightInTheMiddleOfIt

Buck #3: 164 inch @hunt_fe_hill Trinity River Bottom Buck. 

I’ve had some unforgettable memories down at The Hill over the years and this buck and trip was one of the highlights. My biggest TX buck to date and one I’ll never forget! 
Special thanks to Bobby Merchant on the mount.

6 months into my first publishing deal, @coleswindell @aaronjgoodvin and I wrote ‘Out Like That’, which would later be recorded by @lukebryan and become my very first cut as a songwriter. I’ll never forget the feeling walking into the studio the day Luke was recording the album and hearing the intro lick to the song as, he walked up and gave me a hug and said “congrats on your first cut, buddy”. That was the moment for me that I knew any and all of my dreams were possible. The album went on to win ACM Album Of The Decade and is approaching 5x’s platinum. #OutLikeThat

After the tornadoes that hit Middle Tennessee yesterday, this song brought on a whole knew meaning for me… Very thankful the worst missed my house, but unfortunately there are a lot of people that weren’t so lucky. There’s not much anyone can say or do when disasters hit, expect pray and lend a helping hand, but I have all the confidence in the world that the people of Middle TN will bounce back stronger than ever. 💪🏻🙏🏻 
Ps- Thank You for those that reached out to make sure I was ok.

Middle Tennessee- don’t miss @jordanwalker2 @adamcraigofficial and myself at the one and only @franklintheatre THIS THURSDAY NIGHT! 

We’ll be cracking jokes, telling stories behind the songs, and we just might even do a Christmas song or two. Get your tickets now! 🎄🎁🎤

Took a little social media hiatus for the past couple of weeks to focus on the things that matter the most in life. I had never really taken a break from the social world, and just felt like it would be a good time to reset and live life as much in the moment as I possibly could. 
2023 was a mixed emotions year for me, and at times, I felt as defeated with my career as I’ve ever been. 
There’s some things about this year though that I wouldn’t trade for the world, and looking forward to what’s ahead in 2024. 🤟🏼
Another @hunt_fe_hill adventure in the books and what a week it was! 🦌🦆🐗

It’s been a long time coming but 2/2/24 my sophomore album “Right In The Middle Of It” comes out. There’s been so much that has went into this project and I can’t wait for y’all to finally hear it! Stick with me y’all, I need you more than ever!
